&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Homerton Univeristy Hospital NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust Registrar in Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term - 6 Month Post with a view to extend&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for Clinical Fellows in Acute Medicine. This post is at Homerton University Hospital, based in Hackney, East London; an exciting and challenging place with a diverse and richly multicultural population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Homerton University hospital is a Foundation Trust and teaching hospital in East London. We are in the middle of Hackney – a diverse and interesting inner city area. It is a Trauma Unit within the North East London trauma Network and was the designated hospital for the 2012 Olympic Games. It is within walking distance to Homerton and Hackney Central Overground stations, with easy access to major transport links.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All emergency admissions are admitted to the Acute Care Unit, which is staffed by a Multi-professional large Acute Care Team, who retains overall responsibility for the whole ward. The unit is busy and sees approximately 13,000 admissions per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role provides an exciting opportunity to work closely with highly skilled and knowledgeable consultants of all specialties with wide scope to learn and enhance acute medicine skills. A wide range of pathology will be seen in the day to day working in the unit, providing experiences both challenging and varied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Homerton Hospital is proud of the training opportunities on offer and we have an excellent record of getting doctors in non-training posts into training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAnnilie DewarJob titleOperations ManagerEmail addressannilie.dewar@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
